definition: to repair/to patch/to mend/to make up for/to fill (a vacancy)/to supplement
complementary base pairing e.g. adenine A 腺嘌呤 pairs with thymine T 胸腺嘧啶 in DNA
pinyin: jian3 ji1 hu4 bu3 pei4 dui4

sentences.english: Complementary colors make white lights when two are mixed.

sentences.english: Wu noted that the two economies are complementary to each other and share huge potentials in the economic and trade cooperation.

sentences.english: These are complementary concerns and presuppose each other.

sentences.english: How can China utilize such kind of complementarities to develop the cooperation with South Asia?

sentences.english: Likewise, good sales promotion activities are complementary to branding.
sentences.chinese: 同样，好的促销活动对品牌起到互补作用。

sentences.english: I think they are very complementary.
sentences.chinese: 我想他们是非常互补的。

sentences.english: First, we should tap the potential for cooperation and strengthen the complementary advantages.

sentences.english: The multitude that dibble seeding covers and TV crowd have very good complementary sex.

sentences.english: Spring early fall short long hot summer winter-temperature complementary.

sentences.english: In addition, we also examine whether there is any substitutive or complementary relation between diploma and certifications ?

sentences.english: The use of complementary colors is an important aspect of aesthetically pleasing art and graphic design.
sentences.chinese: 使用互补色是美观的艺术设计和平面设计的重要手段。

sentences.english: Third, to give play to complementary advantages and expand economic and trade cooperation.
sentences.chinese: 优势互补，扩大经贸合作。

sentences.english: First, to realize advantageous complementarities and promote common development.
sentences.chinese: 第一，实现优势互补，促进共同发展。
